Alpinia officinarum

   [3054.jpg]
    Authority   Hance
      Family    Liliopsida:Zingiberidae:Zingiberales:Zingiberaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3054

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herb reaching 1-1.5 m in height with subterraneous,
   creeping, copiously branched rhizomes. Rhizomes 8-12 mm in diameter,
   hard, shining, dark brown to black. USES The rhizome is used as a spice
   and it also has medicinal properties. The fruit is used as a substitute
   for true cardamom. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES Lesser
   galangal. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: Languas officinarum. Lesser
   galangal is native of China.

   Sources
   Westphal E 1989 pp 33-34 [FER, TEXT, LIG]
   Duke J 1974 pp 6 [PH, TEMP, RAIN]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 394 [USE]
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 520 [USE]

